Bafana Bafana coach Shakes Mashaba will not join the team on their trip to Mozambique for a friendly international tomorrow.Instead Mashaba faces a disciplinary hearing for what Safa termed a regrettable incident at Peter Mokaba Stadium where South Africa beat Senegal 2-1 in their 2018 World Cup qualifier on Saturday.Assistant coach Owen da Gama will take charge of the national team for the friendly match against Mozambique in Maputo.Safa refused to be drawn on Mashaba s misdemeanour.Mashaba is understood to be facing charges for his unsavoury public utterances. As is our custom in matters such as these, the association will not be making any further comments on this matter out of respect for the dignity of the head coach and the association and the legally privileged nature of such proceedings , Safa said.It s speculated Mashaba could be in hot water for saying the following about the win against Senegal: What does this win mean to me? It s a second lease of life. I was dead already. Kgomosto Sethusha